11/11/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Admiral Gregory G. Johnson, commander in chief of Allied Forces Southern Europe, met on Monday (10 November) with Defence Minister Vlado Buckovski and urged Macedonia to speed up reforms if it wants to receive an invitation to join NATO at the May summit in Istanbul. In Skopje, Johnson reiterated that NATO is ready to provide full assistance on the path towards implementing crucial defence reforms during the next six months. He also praised the work of Macedonia's contingent deployed in Iraq. (A1 TV, Sitel TV - 10/11/03)
